Definition: The operators have been replaced with new symbols. Wherever you see '@', do addition operation and similarly wherever you see '#', do the subtraction operation.

Positive Examples.explanation: Here, '@' represents addition operation. So, the answer is 23 (6+17=23).
Here, '@' represents addition operation and '#' represents subtraction operation. So, the answer is 8 (25-20+3=8).

Negative Examples.explanation: Here, '@' represents addition operation and '#' represents subtraction operation. So, the answer should have been 32 (15+20-3=32) instead of 18.
